# Mixed-vendor golden test (TestEngine_MixedEnvGolden) needs one sample
# secret per rule below. Values are placeholders only in git — replace
# locally with fabricated test keys before running fixture tests:
#
#   stripe-access-token      → sk_test_… or rk_test_…
#   aws-access-token         → AKIA… (20-char access key id)
#   github-personal-access-token → ghp_… (40 chars total)
#   slack-bot-token          → xoxb-…
#   anthropic-api-key        → sk-ant-api03-…
#   google-api-key           → AIzaSy… (39 chars)
#   jwt                      → eyJ….eyJ….… (three base64url segments)
#   generic-high-entropy     → high-entropy token near KEY/TOKEN/SECRET
#
# Do not commit real credentials. See engine_test.go for expected rule IDs.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=SAMPLE_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY_REPLACE_ME
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=SAMPLE_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID_REPLACE_ME
GITHUB_TOKEN=SAMPLE_GITHUB_TOKEN_REPLACE_ME
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=SAMPLE_SLACK_BOT_TOKEN_REPLACE_ME
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=SAMPLE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_REPLACE_ME
GOOGLE_API_KEY=SAMPLE_GOOGLE_API_KEY_REPLACE_ME
JWT=SAMPLE_JWT_REPLACE_ME
INTERNAL_API_TOKEN=SAMPLE_INTERNAL_API_TOKEN_REPLACE_ME
